                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10"> 
                            A round ends when a player either steals their winning tile or draws it, and calls "Mahjong!" 
                            If two players both call Mahjong on the same discard tile, the one closest to the discarder wins the tie-breaker. 
                            The winning hand is scored, the losers pay the winner, and then the tiles are stirred and another round begins.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10"> 
                            If the dealer wins, they get to deal again. 
                            If they did not win, the dealer rotates counter-clockwise. 
                            Since the dealer's Lucky Wind is always East, all the players' Lucky Winds rotate as well. 
                            East player becomes North, South becomes East, West becomes South, and North becomes West.
                        </TextBlock>
                        <Image Source="/Assets/learn-to-play/wind-rotation.png" />

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,0,0,30"> 
                            there's also the Prevailing Wind to keep track of. 
                            The game always begins with East as the Prevailing Wind, and it stays that way until dealer duty has made it around the table and the original dealer deals again. 
                            At that point, Prevailing Wind changes from East to South (then West, then North). 
                            For example: If the dealer doesn't win any of the first four rounds, Prevailing Wind would shift from East to South on the fifth round. 
                            But if the dealer won the second round, the Prevailing Wind wouldn't change until the sixth round.
                        </TextBlock>
